timeline.bodyText: NIT: I see this being used in 1 place. Was there any reason to making this a separate class?
timeline.author: maaquib

replies.bodyText: I didn't found any suitable class to add this change and also to keep future platform-specific utils functions at a single place.
replies.author: dhaniram-kshirsagar

timeline.bodyText: NIT: Do we really need this as a configurable param?
timeline.author: maaquib

replies.bodyText: Yes, at present it is set to 9000, some of the ports in this range were in use by some other processes. Hence, keeping this as an option.
replies.author: dhaniram-kshirsagar
